what you're getting into,

00:41:32.250 --> 00:41:34.700
before taking a step
like that, and saying,

00:41:34.700 --> 00:41:35.930
I'm going to do this.

00:41:35.930 --> 00:41:37.280
JENNIFER PAHLKA: Right.

00:41:37.280 --> 00:41:39.560
Sure, so yeah.

00:41:39.560 --> 00:41:42.220
No, most people don't--
aren't working on something

00:41:42.220 --> 00:41:45.660
that's on the front page of
the paper every single day,

00:41:45.660 --> 00:41:47.750
and therefore is pretty intense.

00:41:47.750 --> 00:41:51.630
In fact, I wish in many
cases that more projects

00:41:51.630 --> 00:41:53.440
